-- Croatian Bad Loans at Banks Rise to 14% at End September
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-11-16T08:22:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-16/croatian-bad-loans-at-banks-rise-to-14-at-end-september.html
Croatian non-performing loans held
by banks rose to 14 percent, or 40 billion kuna ($6.8 billion),
at the end of September, the  central bank  said on its website
yesterday.  The amount of bad loans to companies, the public sector and
citizens was at 13.3 percent at the end of June, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
